<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1239,1380,1821,1855]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Praomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="206" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tullbergi">P. tullbergi</taxonomicName>
included P. misonne: from Central Africa, which was shown to be distinct, thereby restricting 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[939,1074,1939,1973]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Praomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="206" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tullbergi">P. tullbergi</taxonomicName>
to West Africa west of Volta River and 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1174,1983,2012]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Praomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="206" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="misonnei">P. misonnei</taxonomicName>
to the east of
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
